2:T5db,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Which venues are supported?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Deribit, OKX, Binance, Bybit, Thalex, Derive, Coincall, and Gate.io — options books, normalized to one schema and one set of conventions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How fast is the feed?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Sub-second across every venue. Quotes, greeks, and route candidates update tick-by-tick with an explicit latency budget surfaced in the UI."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can we plug in our own signals?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Internal marks, risk overlays, and desk-specific enrichment merge into the same surface so routing reflects your stack, not a generic market view."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Browser or desktop?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Terminal-first. Delivery shape is decided per desk, but the UX is built to feel like a serious pro tool — not a dashboard."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens when a venue goes down?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Degraded feeds show as degraded in the UI. Venue health, route confidence, and stale-quote flags are first-class surface elements."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is there an API?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The platform is built around command-driven workflows and extensible hooks. API surface and automation scope are shaped during onboarding."}}]}0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"landing-page min-h-screen bg-[var(--landing-bg)] text-[var(--landing-text)]","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$2"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Oggregator\",\"url\":\"https://oggregator.xyz\"}"}}],["$","a",null,{"href":"#main","class